data.name: CPF generator
data.description:
CPF is a Brazilian identification document.</br>
It consists of 11 digits, where the 10th and 11th are checked against a calculation of the others.</br>
In this kata you need to create out the 10th and 11th numbers, basic front-end developers validations method</br>
</br>
10th element is the of the sum of (`first*10+second*9...ninth*2`) multiplied 10 mod 11, if is 10 = 0
</br></br>
11th element is the of the sum of (`first*11+second*10...tenth*2`) multiplied 10 mod 11, if is 10 = 0
</br></br>
Example1:</br>
input ("cpf") is "123.456.789-xx"</br>
To check the 10th you must:</br>
`1*10 + 2*9 + 3*8 + 4*7 + 5*6 + 6*5 + 7*4 + 8*3 + 9*2` multiply this by 10, and do the modulus by 11, giving 10 , which will be considered 0, from 1-9 the 10th CPF number will be the result itself</br>
To check the 11th you must:</br>
`1*11 + 2*10 + 3*9 + 4*8 + 5*7 + 6*6 + 7*5 + 8*4 + 9*3 + 0*2` multiply by 10 and then find its modulus by 11
Thus, the CPF of this case will be:</br>
Output result is "123.456.789-09"</br></br>
Example2:</br>
input ("cpf") is "111.111.111-xx"</br>
For 10th:</br>
`1*10 + 1*9 + 1*8 + 1*7 + 1*6 + 1*5 + 1*4 + 1*3 + 1*2` multiply by 10 and then find its modulus by 11</br>
10th=1</br>
For 11th:</br>
`1*11 + 1*10 + 1*9 + 1*8 + 1*7 + 1*6 + 1*5 + 1*4 + 1*3 + 1*2` multiply by 10 and then find its modulus by 11</br>
11th=1</br>
Output result is "111.111.111-11"
